February 3, 2026
2
3 SENATE BILL NO. 1923 By: Murdock
4
5
6 An Act relating to prisons and reformatories;
defining term; prohibiting access to social media
7 platforms by inmates; authorizing the Department of
Corrections to promulgate rules; providing for
8 codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 568.1 of Title 57, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. For the purposes of this section, “social media platform”
16 means a website or Internet medium that:
17 1. Permits a person to become a registered user, establish an
18 account, or create a profile for the purpose of allowing users to
19 create, share, and view user-generated content through such an
20 account or profile;
21 2. Enables one or more users to generate content that can be
22 viewed by other users of the medium; and
23 3. Primarily serves as a medium for users to interact with
24 content generated by other users of the medium.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1923 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 B. 1. The Department of Corrections shall prohibit inmates
2 from accessing social media platforms on any cellular phone, tablet,
3 computer, or other electronic device provided by the Department.
4 2. The Department of Corrections shall promulgate rules to
5 effectuate the provisions of this section.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
7 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC SAFETY
February 3, 2026 - DO PASS
